HEADWORD: Pus
<hw>Pus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., akin to Gr. <?/, <?/,
and to E. <ets>foul</ets>: cf. F. <ets>pus</ets>. See <er>Foul</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The yellowish white opaque
creamy matter produced by the process of suppuration. It consists of
innumerable white nucleated cells floating in a clear liquid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

